>> is religion this aspect is not touched in FHS :-((
>
>debian does not have a "perl-based startup system" (or if it does,
>you have to go override the default and install something other than
>sysvinit).
When I first started with Debian (bo, 1.3), the `start-stop-daemon' 
program was written in perl, but nothing else in the init scripts 
used/uses perl. `start-stop-daemon' in now written in C, and has been 
since hamm (Debian 2.0).
